messages.speech: Jagdish Temple: It is a large Hindu temple in the middle of Udaipur in Rajasthan, just outside the royal palace. It has been in continuous worship since 1651. A big tourist attraction, the temple was originally called the temple of Jagannath Rai but is now called Jagdish-ji. It is a major monument in Udaipur.                                                                                                              For more info: www.udaipur.org.uk/temples/jagdish-temple.html
